    <div id="about">
      <h1>Dropoff</h1>
      <p>
        Dropoff is a simple text-dropoff application. Provide some text in the above textarea and click <em>Dropoff</em>. The text will be stored and a 32 character key will be provided as a lookup.
      </p>
      <h3>Fetch</h3>
      <p>To fetch the text "Dropped off", simply put the 32 character key in the url behind the url.</p>
      <p>
        e.x. <a href="https://dropoff.azurewebsites.net/00000000000000000000000000000000">
          <code>https://dropoff.azurewebsites.net/00000000000000000000000000000000</code>
        </a>
      </p>
      <h4>Content Types</h4>
      <p>
        To fetch a file as a different content type: <a href="https://dropoff.azurewebsites.net/00000000000000000000000000000000?t=html">
          <code>
            https://dropoff.azurewebsites.net/00000000000000000000000000000000?<strong>t=html</strong>
          </code>
        </a>
      </p>
      <p>Available content types:</p>
      <ul>
        <li>
          <strong>raw</strong> : "text/plain"
        </li>
        <li>
          <strong>html</strong> : "text/html"
        </li>
        <li>
          <strong>json</strong> : "application/json"
        </li>
      </ul>
      <h3>Notices</h3>
      <ul>
        <li>There is a 4MB limit for files provided.</li>
        <li>This is just a simple web application, to learn some new back-end technologies.</li>
        <li>The files/text/information you provide, you provide at will. I reserve the right to modify and delete any files/text/information you may provide.</li>
      </ul>
    </div>
